{
  "texts": [
    "Valence Rules: This approach focuses on combinations of atoms adhering to valence rules.",
    "An example is GDB-17 (55), which lists all organic molecules with up to 17 atoms of C, N, O, and S. 2.",
    "Fragment Spaces: Techniques like BRICS (75) and RECAP (76) employ sets of small molecular fragments that are linked together through a set of manually defined rules. 3.",
    "Synthon Method: Proposed in 2007 (77), it uses generalized reactions on available reagents to enumerate synthetically accessible molecules.",
    "Notable methodologies include DOGS (78), Synth-On (79), and pre-compiled commercial libraries (80, 81). 4."
  ]
}